ID: TCASE-18151
Name: Branch Handling
*Branch Handling*

Verify branch handling by modifying branch state, i.e. enabling and disabling selected branches.

Limitations:
Limited to Active Star Transceivers. Single Transceivers don't have branches and the APIs perform no action

Preconditions:
none.

Test Steps:
# Call {{FrTrcv_DisableTransceiverBranch}} with FrTrcv_BranchIdx 0
# Assert that no frames are sent on branch 0
# Call {{FrTrcv_EnableTransceiverBranch}} with FrTrcv_BranchIdx 0
# Assert that frames are sent on branch 0
# Call {{FrTrcv_DisableTransceiverBranch}} with FrTrcv_BranchIdx 4
# Assert that no frames are sent on branch 4
# Call {{FrTrcv_EnableTransceiverBranch}} with FrTrcv_BranchIdx 4
# Assert that frames are sent on branch 4

ID: TCASE-18152
Name: Wakeup detection
*Wakeup detection*

Verify wake up detection

It is verified that {{FrTrcv_CheckWakeupByTransceiver}} or {{FrTrcv_MainFunction}} calls the EcuM when a wakeup event (internal or external) is detected on the bus. Additionally the wake up reason is checked for correctness.

Precondition:
Transceiver is in Low Power mode
Wake up detection is enabled

Test Steps:
# Call {{FrTrcv_SetTransceiverMode}} with FrTrcv_TrcvMode = FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_STANDBY mode
# Trigger Wake Up detection of driver by calling {{FrTrcv_MainFunction}} or {{FrTrcv_CheckWakeupByTransceiver}} depending whether polling or interrupt mode is configured
# Assert that EcuM is not called
# Get Wakeup Reason by calling {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverWUReason}}
# Assert wakeup reason to be FRTRCV_WU_RESET or FRTRCV_WU_NOT_SUPPORTED depending if wake up detection is enabled on channel
#
# Call {{FrTrcv_SetTransceiverMode}} with FrTrcv_TrcvMode = FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_STANDBY mode
# Send remote Wake Up pattern
# Trigger Wake Up detection of driver by calling {{FrTrcv_MainFunction}} or {{FrTrcv_CheckWakeupByTransceiver}} depending whether polling or interrupt mode is configured
# Assert that EcuM is called with the configured WakeupSourceRef
# Get Wakeup Reason by calling {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverWUReason}}
# Assert wakeup reason to be FRTRCV_WU_BY_BUS or FRTRCV_WU_NOT_SUPPORTED depending if wake up detection is enabled on channel
#
# Call {{FrTrcv_SetTransceiverMode}} with FrTrcv_TrcvMode = FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_SLEEP mode
# Send local Wake Up
# Trigger Wake Up detection of driver by calling {{FrTrcv_MainFunction}} or {{FrTrcv_CheckWakeupByTransceiver}} depending whether polling or interrupt mode is configured
# Assert that EcuM is called with the configured WakeupSourceRef
# Get Wakeup Reason
# Assert wakeup reason to be FRTRCV_WU_BY_PIN or FRTRCV_WU_NOT_SUPPORTED depending if wake up detection is enabled on channel
#
# Clear transceiver wake up by calling {{FrTrcv_ClearTransceiverWakeup}}
# Get Wakeup Reason by calling {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverWUReason}}
# Assert wakeup reason to be FRTRCV_WU_RESET
#
# call {{FrTrcv_SetTransceiverMode}} with FrTrcv_TrcvMode = FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_NORMAL mode
# Get Wakeup Reason by calling {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverWUReason}}
# Assert wakeup reason to be FRTRCV_WU_INTERNALLY or FRTRCV_WU_NOT_SUPPORTED depending if wake up detection is enabled on channel

ID: TCASE-20848
Name: Error detection
*Error detection*

Verify error detection

it is verified that error detection and reporting works as specified. As the error detection capability is Trcv specific no details about the error reason are given here. A plausible error condition must be chosen which can be detected by the device.

Precondition:
Bus error diagnosis is enabled

Test Steps:
# Call {{FrTrcv_SetTransceiverMode}} to set the Transceiver in NORMAL mode
# Create error condition/collision on bus, e.g. short cut, collision (Trcv dependent)
# Call {{FrTrcv_MainFunction}} or {{FrTrcv_CheckWakeupByTransceiver}} depending whether polling or interrupt mode is configured to trigger detection
# Assert that either {{Dem_ReportErrorStatus}} or {{Appl_FrTrcv_ReportErrorStatusPreFailed}} (depending on FRTRCV_TRCV_DEM_CALLBACK switch) is called with error code {{FRTRCV_E_FR_ERRN_TRCV}} with {{DEM_EVENT_STATUS_PREFAILED}}
# Get Error Reason by calling {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverError}}
# Assert that FRTRCV_BDE_GLOBAL is set
# Assert that the error reason (e.g. FRTRCV_BDE_NOISE) is set
# Assert that the API returned E_OK
# Remove error condition
# Perform {{FrTrcv_MainFunction}} or {{FrTrcv_CheckWakeupByTransceiver}} depending whether polling or interrupt mode is configured to trigger detection
# Assert that either {{Dem_ReportErrorStatus}} or {{Appl_FrTrcv_ReportErrorStatusPrePassed}} (depending on FRTRCV_TRCV_DEM_CALLBACK switch) is called with error code {{FRTRCV_E_FR_ERRN_TRCV}} with {{DEM_EVENT_STATUS_PREPASSED}}

ID: TCASE-363434
Name: Multi Channel
*Multi Channel*

it is verified that the Transceiver driver can handle independent devices in a multi channel configuration.

Precondition:
Configuration has at least two channels

Test Steps:
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_SetTransceiverMode}} to set transceiver mode FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_NORMAL on channel 0.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_SetTransceiverMode}} to set transceiver mode FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_STANDBY on channel 1.
# Assert that DIO pin EN_A is STD_HIGH.
# Assert that DIO pin STBN_A is STD_HIGH.
# Assert that DIO pin EN_B is STD_LOW.
# Assert that DIO pin STBN_B is STD_LOW.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_SetTransceiverMode}} to set transceiver mode FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_STANDBY on channel 0.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_ClearTransceiverWakeup}} on channel 0.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_ClearTransceiverWakeup}} on channel 1.
# Apply remote wake up on channel 1.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_CheckWakeupByTransceiver}} on channel 0.
# Assert that the EcuM was not called.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_CheckWakeupByTransceiver}} on channel 1.
# Assert that the EcuM was called with the correct Wake up Source Ref if wake up detection is enabled.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_GetTransceiverWUReason}} to get the wake up reason on channel 0.
# Assert that the wake up reason is FRTRCV_WU_RESET.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_GetTransceiverWUReason}} to get the wake up reason on channel 1.
# Assert that the wake up reason is FRTRCV_WU_BY_BUS if wake up detection is enabled, otherwise FRTRCV_WU_RESET.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_SetTransceiverMode}} to set transceiver mode FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_NORMAL on channel 0.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_SetTransceiverMode}} to set transceiver mode FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_NORMAL on channel 1.
# Apply  a Bus error on channel 1.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_CheckWakeupByTransceiver}} on channel 0.
# Assert that DEM is not called.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_CheckWakeupByTransceiver}} on channel 1.
# Assert that the DEM is called with DEM_EVENT_STATUS_PREFAILED and the correct DEM failure reason.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_GetTransceiverError}} to get the error reason on cahnnel 0.
# Assert that no error is reported.
# Call {{FrTrcv_30_Tja1080_GetTransceiverError}} to get the error reason on cahnnel 1.
# Assert that the FRTRCV_30_TJA1080_BDE_GLOBAL flag is set.
# Assert the the specific bus error reason is reported as applied.

4 Test of component abstract designTest Overview
4.2 Test of state-machinesTest Overview
ID: TCASE-20997
Name: Mode Change
*Mode Change*

Verify mode change
The Transceiver Driver supports the modes and transitions as described in the following picture.
!https://vglobpessvn1.vg.vector.int/svn/CANbedded/DrvTransBase/DrvTrans__coreFrxAsr/trunk/_doc/20_Design/WorkingProducts/FrTrcv_smModes.png!
The following limitations apply:
- Optionals modes (SLEEP, RECEIVE_ONLY) can be substituted by the corresponding mode (STANDBY, NORMAL) if not supported by HW.
- Real mode is returned by FrTrcv_GetTransceiverMode

It is verified that all transitions can be taken and that the respective/supported mode is entered. It is implicitly tested if DIO calls work as the set mode is read back to verify the actual mode. This also includes the application call-back DIO. They must forward the requests to the stub based DIO module

Precondition:
none.

Test Steps:
# Call {{FrTrcv_Init}} to initialize component
# Call {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverMode}} to get current Trcv mode
# Assert if configured initial mode is set
# For all 17 transitions (transition to initial mode and 16 inter mode transitions) do:
## Call {{FrTrcv_SetTransceiverMode}} to set the respective mode
## Call {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverMode}} to get current Trcv mode
## Assert if mode is as set
# Please note that:
# Assert if mode is {{FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_SLEEP}} or {{FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_STANDBY}} if sleep mode is not supported by Transceiver
# Assert if mode is {{FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_RECEIVEONLY}} or {{FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_NORMAL}} if Receive Only mode is not supported by Transceiver
# Call {{FrTrcv_SetTransceiverMode}} to set {{FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_ILLEGAL}} which is not one of the defined states
# Call {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverMode}} to get current Trcv mode
# Assert if mode is unchanged
# Call {{FrTrcv_Phy_SetMode}} to set an undefined mode
# Assert that E_NOT_OK is returned

Overview
TestRun Overview

Name: Wakeup detection during Sleep transition
*Wakeup detection during Sleep transition*

Verify wake up detection during Sleep transition

It is verified that {{FrTrcv_SetTransceiverMode}} calls the EcuM after a transition to sleep mode and when a wakeup event (internal or external) is detected on the bus.

Precondition:
Wake up detection is enabled

Test Steps:

# Assert that EcuM is not called
# Send remote Wake Up pattern
# Call {{FrTrcv_SetTransceiverMode}} with FrTrcv_TrcvMode = FRTRCV_TRCVMODE_SLEEP
# Assert that EcuM is called with the configured WakeupSourceRef
# Get Wakeup Reason by calling {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverWUReason}}
# Assert wakeup reason to be FRTRCV_WU_BY_BUS or FRTRCV_WU_NOT_SUPPORTED depending if wake up detection is enabled on channel

Name: Verify DET check - uninitialized
*Verify DET check - uninitialized*

Verify DET checks of each API except {{FfTrcv_Init}}, {{FrTrcv_InitMemory}} and {{FrTrcv_GetVersionInfo}} while the component is not initialized. All DET parameters (Module ID, Instance ID, API ID and Error ID = UNINIT) are checked for validity after a function call.

Precondition:
FrTrcv_InitMemory is called
FrTrcv_Init() is not called - component is uninitialized
FRTRCV_DEV_ERROR_DETECT is STD_ON
FRTRCV_DEV_ERROR_REPORT is STD_ON

Test Steps:
# Assert that DET error is thrown and parameters are valid when calling {{FrTrcv_SetTransceiverMode}}
# Assert that the return value of service {{FrTrcv_SetTransceiverMode}} is E_NOT_OK
# Assert that DET error is thrown and parameters are valid when calling {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverMode}}
# Assert that the return value of service {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverMode}} is E_NOT_OK
# Assert that DET error is thrown and parameters are valid when calling {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverWUReason}}
# Assert that the return value of service {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverWUReason}} is E_NOT_OK

# Assert that the return value of service {{FrTrcv_ClearTransceiverWakeup}} is E_NOT_OK
# Assert that DET error is thrown and parameters are valid when calling {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverError}}
# Assert that the return value of service {{FrTrcv_GetTransceiverError}} is E_NOT_OK
# Assert that no DET error is thrown when calling {{FrTrcv_CheckWakeupByTransceiver}}
# Assert that no DET error is thrown when calling {{FrTrcv_MainFunction}}
#if Active Star Transceiver
# Assert that DET error is thrown and parameters are valid when calling {{FrTrcv_DisableTransceiverBranch}}
# Assert that the return value of service {{FrTrcv_DisableTransceiverBranch}} is E_NOT_OK
# Assert that DET error is thrown and parameters are valid when calling {{FrTrcv_EnableTransceiverBranch}}
# Assert that the return value of service {{FrTrcv_EnableTransceiverBranch}} is E_NOT_OK
#else
# Assert that the return value of service {{FrTrcv_DisableTransceiverBranch}} is E_NOT_OK
# Assert that the return value of service {{FrTrcv_EnableTransceiverBranch}} is E_OK
#endif
